title: >
  NeuroForge: A Governed Neuro-Cognitive Architecture with Auditable
  Internal Change and Bounded Self-Revision

abstract: >
  NeuroForge is a neuro-cognitive research architecture designed to make
  internal state, internal change, and internal justifications observable
  and auditable over time. It integrates a spiking-inspired neural
  substrate with symbolic language grounding, persistent episodic,
  semantic, and procedural memory, and metacognitive governance layers
  including reflection, goal coherence, self-trust, self-explanation,
  and bounded self-revision.
  
  The system prioritizes architecture-first governance, traceability,
  and safety-bounded learning over benchmark performance. NeuroForge is
  intentionally frozen at Stage C v1, permitting learning without
  authority escalation, and serves as a reference implementation for
  governed learning systems rather than an autonomous agent or product.

